The paper proposes a technique for training robotic tasks through sequential subtasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural networks to represent the local control policies suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm's utilization of the value function aligns with the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's application to continuous control problems for dynamic systems suggests a potential overlap with computer vision (cs.CV) in terms of perception and sensing.
